.Im MicroEmacs modes
.so me.tni
.TH fence 2m
.XI fence - "Auto fence matching mode"
.SH NAME
fence \- Auto fence matching mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "fence Mode"
.sp
\fBf\fR \- mode line letter.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fence
mode can be used to enable or disable  the  automatic  displaying  of and open
fence when the corresponding  closing fence is typed. When the mode is enabled
and the closing fence is typed the cursor is temporarily  move to the position
of the opening fence. The duration of the move can be controlled by the
.Ht $fmatchdelay 5
variable; any user input interrupts the display.
.PP
If
.Ht cmode 2m
is also enabled the search algorithm used is '\fIC\fR' aware and if a matching
fence is not found then the bell is rung as a warning. If  \fBcmode\fR  is not
enable any closing fence which cannot be matched is ignored.
.SH NOTES
The following characters are considered closing fences:
.CS
}  )  ]
.CE
These are match with the following opening fences respectively:
.CS
{  (  [
.CE
In \*(mE then the use of fence mode has been depreciated. Matching fence
hilighting has been implemented as a macro and is invoked as part of the
buffer set up operation of
.Ht buffer-init 3 .
